general.descriptionRatGod: Rat God will help you in Escape From Tarkov, by accessing in-game information and delivering it to you!
general.permissionsRatGod:
Rat God's minimum permissions requirements are:
Use Application Commands.
Send Messages.
Embed Links.
Attach Files.
Read message history.

null.value:
Detailed map: **/Maps Customs Map**.
Guide for hidden stashes: **/Maps Customs Hidden Stashes**.
Interactive map: **/Maps Customs Interactive Map**.
Dorms map: **/Maps Customs Dorms**.
3D map: **/Maps Customs 3D**.

Info.name: Description
Info.value: A large area of industrial park land situated adjacent to the factory. This area houses a customs terminal, fuel storage facilities, offices, and dorms as well as a variety of other infrastructure buildings.

Info.name: Features
Info.value:
**The Dorms** are two buildings located in the southernmost area of the map. The eastern building is three stories tall while the western building is two stories tall. Each structure boasts a front entrance and a fire escape at each end with doorways leading to each floor (some of which are blocked or permanently locked). These dorms are the location of many Quests and unlockable rooms.

**Construction** is a two story concrete frame of a building. This structure had a wide view of the river crossing and bridge.

**New Gas Station** is a building at the western side of the map, near the main road. The building has two unlockable rooms in it.

**Military Checkpoint** is at the end of the road past the Gas Station. This point has many Scavs and is the only location with easy access through the wall to the extraction zones.

**ZB-1013 or Stronghold** is at the northern end of the map and features a unlockable extract; loot; and views of crackhouse, construction and the train crossing.

Info.name: Boss
Info.value: **Name:** Reshala.

Info.name: Locations
Info.value:
Marked circles on the map.
In the "Dorms", in the "New Gas Station", or in the "Scav Stronghold"
Rarely at the tower south of the "New Gas Station"
Rarely at the passage between Checkpoint and Sub-Station.

Info.name: Health
Info.value: 752 Total, Head: 62, Thorax: 145, Stomach: 125, Arms: 100 each, Legs: 110 each.

Info.name: Followers
Info.value: Following Reshala around are 4 heavily armed guards.

Info.name: Suggestions
Info.value: Leave suggestions about what else would be nice to have inside of this command.

Interactive map: **/Maps Factory Interactive Map**.

Info.name: Description
Info.value:
The industrial estate and facilities of chemical factory #16 were rented out illegally to the TerraGroup company.
During the Contract Wars, this factory was a hotbed for numerous firefights between USEC and BEAR operatives that determined control over the entire Tarkov industrial district.
With time, the factory premises were converted into a shelter for local civilians, Scavs, along with the occasional USEC or BEAR operators.

Info.name: Features
Info.value: A small, fast-paced CQC map inside of a multi-story industrial factory, complete with tunnels and overhead walkways.

Info.value: **Name:** Tagilla.

Info.name: Locations
Info.value: Nearby the pit and underground sections.

Info.name: Description
Info.value: The South interchange is a key location for transport in the city. This strategic area connects the port and harbor with the industrial outskirts of Tarkov. Located in the center of the interchange is a huge ULTRA shopping mall which was used as the main base of operation for the EMERCOM evacuation.

Info.name: Features
Info.value:
Three anchor stores:
**IDEA** (a furniture store)
**OLI** (a hardware store)
**Goshan** (a grocery store).

Many small stores that sell a wide variety of products including electronics, clothing, exercise equipment, firearms, and food.

Outside there is a go-kart track, large parking lots, small wooded areas, and numerous roads.

A fully linked illumination grid, able to be switched on at the [power station](https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/escapefromtarkov_gamepedia/images/c/c5/Power_switch.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/1000?cb=20200312223921).

Alarms around some stores and a triggerable alarm at the Kiba Arms Store. The alarms can be switched off at designated terminals:

Info.name: Alarm switches
Info.value:
[2F Alarm switch](https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/escapefromtarkov_gamepedia/images/8/83/Inter_alarm_terminal.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/1000?cb=20200312221706) and [1F Alarm switch](https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/escapefromtarkov_gamepedia/images/a/aa/Inter_alarm_terminal_2.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/1000?cb=20200312221936)
[Alarm Switch Map](https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/escapefromtarkov_gamepedia/images/e/ec/Interchange_alarm_map.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/1000?cb=20200314130950).

null.value:
Detailed map: **/Maps Lighthouse Map**.
Guide for hidden stashes: **/Maps Lighthouse Hidden Stashes**.
Interactive map: **/Maps Lighthouse Interactive Map**.

Info.name: Description
Info.value: The lighthouse at Cape Dalniy was an important strategic object on the way to Tarkov. During Contract Wars, it was the main entry point for USEC units and served as their base of operations. After the conflict, Scavs took a fancy to this place, until the old owners returned, who decided to stay in Tarkov and establish their own order.

Info.name: Features
Info.value:
Lighthouse is the only map to include the [Rogues](https://escapefromtarkov.fandom.com/wiki/Rogues) faction. At the Water treatment plant, Rogues are stationed on machine gun and grenade launcher emplacements, with patrols around the area. Guards will perform suppressive fire on enemies who come too close. Players on the [USEC](https://escapefromtarkov.fandom.com/wiki/USEC) faction, however, will not be opened fire upon immediately, unless they are in a group with a [BEAR](https://escapefromtarkov.fandom.com/wiki/BEAR). Instead, the Rogues will tell the player to leave the area, only shooting at them if they do not leave. If a USEC player fights the Rogues, they will be treated as hostile by them for the next few raids.
The lighthouse itself is not reachable - the bridge connecting the mainland to the lighthouse is covered by a sniper which will shoot and kill players if they try to cross.

Info.name: Boss
Info.value: There is no boss on this map, but there are [Rogues](https://escapefromtarkov.fandom.com/wiki/Rogues) patrolling the area. Rogues often patrol in pairs, and will employ highly accurate suppressive fire while pushing players.

Info.name: Suggestions
Info.value: Leave suggestions about what else would be nice to have inside of this command.

Info.name: Description
Info.value: The secret Federal State Reserve Agency base that, according to urban legend, contains enough supplies to last for years: food, medications and other resources, enough to survive an all-out nuclear war.

Info.name: Features
Info.value: Mounted, static weaponry in the form of the [AGS grenade launcher](https://escapefromtarkov.fandom.com/wiki/AGS-30_30x29mm_automatic_grenade_launcher) and [NSV machine gun](https://escapefromtarkov.fandom.com/wiki/NSV_%22Utyos%22_12.7x108_heavy_machine_gun).

Info.name: Description
Info.value: Shoreline is a large area located on the coastal outskirts of Tarkov, next to the city's port. The area's geography features tracts of undulating woodland, large open fields, jagged cliffs, a swamp and a long stretch of shoreline. Significant man made points of interest include a partially abandoned village, a modern residential development, a boating facility, a gas station, a weather station, a cellular communications tower and the focal point of the map, the Azure Coast Health Resort. This luxury compound consists of three multi-story buildings and was once used as temporary accommodation by members of TerraGroup and its associated divisions as they prepared for the evacuation of Tarkov Port. When operational, the resort draws power from a nearby hydroelectric plant.

Info.name: Features
Info.value: Shoreline is the second largest location in [Escape from Tarkov](https://escapefromtarkov.fandom.com/wiki/Escape_from_Tarkov) and contains a plethora of areas for players to explore and loot. The large, varied terrain means players can expect to engage in fire fights at both close quarters and long range.

null.value:
Detailed map: **/Maps Labs Map**.
Interactive map: **/Maps Labs Interactive Map**.
Map for each floor: **/Maps Labs Basement/First Floor/Second Floor**.
3D map: **/Maps Labs 3D**.

Info.name: Description
Info.value: Underground laboratory complex TerraGroup Labs is a secret object right under the center of Tarkov. Officially, this research center does not exist and, based on data scraps, is engaged in R&D, testing and simulation projects in chemistry, physics, biology, and high-tech areas.

Info.name: Features
Info.value:
**Insurance** [doesn't work](https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/escapefromtarkov_gamepedia/images/2/21/TheLab-Insurance-Messages-01.PNG/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/512?cb=20181227203004) on labs.
**Announcer**
Whenever an event of high importance happens inside The Lab, an announcement will be triggered.
There is an announcement for every extraction besides the **Ventilation shaft** and the **Sewage conduit**. The announcement for the parking extraction can be disabled using the [Yellow keycard](https://escapefromtarkov.fandom.com/wiki/TerraGroup_Labs_keycard_(Yellow)).
**Tagged and Cursed**
Unlike other maps in Tarkov, PMCs are not tagged and cursed at the start of a raid on Labs when deploying with no gear or weapons.
You can't go in as a scav on Labs.

Info.name: Boss
Info.value: There is no boss on this map but every single AI is a [Raider](https://escapefromtarkov.fandom.com/wiki/Scav_Raiders). They are dangerous but carry better gear.

Info.value: Leave suggestions about what else would be nice to have inside of this command.
